CAPE TOWN – A vegetation fire broke out on the slopes of Table Mountain on Sunday morning in Cape Town. Four fire engines and three water tankers with 37 firefighters from City's Fire and Rescue Service were on the scene, assisted by Table Mountain National Parks. READ: Cape Town to activate disaster operations centre for Day Zero There were no reports of damage to property and the cause of the blaze remains unknown. No injuries have been reported, while hikers in the Platteklip Gorge area have been evacuated from the mountainside. eNCA